        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer66613624" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12781710827389280158">Here is the quintessential defense of fantasy as a higher form of Art, “a natural human activity,” worthy of adults and children alike. “Fantasy remains a human right: we make in our measure and in our derivative mode, because we are made: and not only made, but made in the image and likeness of a Maker.” Tolkien also lays forth now-famous ideas such as man as Sub-creator, the Consolation of the Happy Ending, Eucatastrophe, and the fairy-story quality of the gospel. A profound and thrilling essa</span>
  <span id="freeText12781710827389280158" style="display:none">Here is the quintessential defense of fantasy as a higher form of Art, “a natural human activity,” worthy of adults and children alike. “Fantasy remains a human right: we make in our measure and in our derivative mode, because we are made: and not only made, but made in the image and likeness of a Maker.” Tolkien also lays forth now-famous ideas such as man as Sub-creator, the Consolation of the Happy Ending, Eucatastrophe, and the fairy-story quality of the gospel. A profound and thrilling essay.</span>
