<div id="review_712650169" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/712650169" />
    <a title="Renada Thompson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10264510-renada-thompson"><img alt="Renada Thompson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339869467p2/10264510.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/712650169?book_show_action=true">Sep 05, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Renada Thompson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Renada Thompson" href="/user/show/10264510-renada-thompson">Renada Thompson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10264510-renada-thompson?shelf=british">british</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10264510-renada-thompson?shelf=read-in-2014">read-in-2014</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10264510-renada-thompson?shelf=worth-rereading">worth-rereading</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer712650169" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13193840004431060552">I had read bits and pieces of this in various forms over the years. Some probably from Tolkien biographies, some in Christian books, maybe it&apos;s even quoted in the Lord of the Rings DVD special features. But it&apos;s certainly worth reading in its entirety, and in the end, explains for me why Tolkien&apos;s trilogy is unmatched in its ability to move me to both deep joy and deep grief while pointing to the <i>Evangelium</i>.</span>
  <span id="freeText13193840004431060552" style="display:none">I had read bits and pieces of this in various forms over the years. Some probably from Tolkien biographies, some in Christian books, maybe it's even quoted in the Lord of the Rings DVD special features. But it's certainly worth reading in its entirety, and in the end, explains for me why Tolkien's trilogy is unmatched in its ability to move me to both deep joy and deep grief while pointing to the <i>Evangelium</i>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13193840004431060552" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


